Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["parallel code explanation", "Section",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.680959148082035*^9, 
  3.680959159961363*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b2dea3df-5cb9-4f12-835a-\
0cf0c965b14b"],

Cell["\<\
explanations:

1) In standard setup the subkernels do not read the init.m file and do
not distribute $Path to subkernels, because subkernels could run on
remote machines where packages are found in different locations.
Hence, normally the user needs to define the proper $Path for the
subkernels manually.

2) However, as soon as any kernel related command is executed, the
Package \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]SubKernels`\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is loaded \
that provides a variable \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]stdargs\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]
that can be changed so that subkernels do read the init.m file.\
\>", "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.570885909441362*^9, 3.570885921762833*^9}, 
   3.57088595830311*^9},ExpressionUUID->"af4148d1-c63a-4d2d-b0d0-\
f24b5f7fc90d"]
}, Closed]],

